5:
Attacking a medical relief ship is a
new low, even for jerks like you!
9:
Aye, you Fellowship of Floof idiots
might be runnin' a charity, but we
sure as hell aren't!
13:
If anyone... *cough*
Deserves those supplies... *wheeze*
It's us!
18:
Whose brilliant idea was it to attack
the people that give FREE AID when
you're that sick?
21:
They won't last long if they keep this
up. We need to pacify them with all
haste!
25: You think you can take us—
32:
Pythica, Fellowship of Floof's newest
nurse, reporting for duty!
35:
I've already finished on the other
side of the ship! Now it's your turn to
get looked at, so why don't you put
those weapons down—
38:
You... *cough*
How dare you do that to our cap'n!
48:
And that's that! Make sure to take
your medicine three times a day
after eating!
51:
By the way, is everything okay with
your ankle? You were keeping it out
of sight, so I wanted to check.
58:
I'll fix it in place for now, since it
seems like it's fractured. I'll have a
closer look at it later. Take care!
63:
...You said you only just joined the
Fellowship, yet you very expertly
treated your patients.
67:
Oh, you think so? I guess it's
because I have some experience,
hehehe!
71:
I used to help out the local doctor
back home, so I can handle
something like that pretty easily!
74:
Still, compared to everyone else in
the Fellowship, I have a long way to
go.
86:
The Fellowship of the Floof treats
everyone and anyone... Which
makes them super cool in my book!
90:
I'm going to do my best to live up to
the reputation we've built!
94: I understand. It is a very cool crew.
101:
Hey, that's enough chatting! I need
someone to take blood over here!
105: Gah! Sorry, I'll be right over!
109: All right, this'll only take a second...
117:
Y-yeah! Just having a hard time
finding the right vein. Must be thin
veins...
120:
You sure you know what you're
doin'? I'm a real wimp when it
comes to pain, so this better not
hurt!
122:
...Let me see that. When you have a
patient with thinner veins, you
should do this instead...
125:
Th-thank you very much for the
help! You got that done so quickly...
128:
Pythica, remember what we told
you? If you're having trouble, don't
be afraid to ask for help.
129:
We know better than anyone that
you wouldn't shirk your duty and
pass it onto someone else.
136: Hey, I need another hand over here!
140: Yeah... Still a long way to go for me...
144:
You needn't be so hard on yourself.
Progress isn't made in a day...
156:
Ah, Vice Captain! I-I swear I'm not
slacking off!
159:
Of course you aren't. Everyone on
this ship knows you wouldn't do that.
161:
I actually just wanted to speak with
you and Alk's crew for a moment.
167:
You want Pythica to train her skills
while traveling with us?
171:
I-is this a polite way to say... I'm
being fired?!
174:
As you can see, Pythica's
self-esteem could use a little work.
176:
It causes her to panic and make
irrational decisions. This could prove
to be a real problem one day.
178:
...I see. You want her to strike out on
her own so she can learn to think
more clearly.
189:
Pythica, I'm assigning you on a
special training mission.
191:
For one month, you'll be serving as
medical staff for Alk and his friends
during their travels.
193:
...See the world. Let yourself relearn
what it means to be a nurse.
196: We're glad to have you aboard!
199:
Traveling with us might prove to be
shocking at first, but I'm certain
you'll grow used to it in no time.
